commitResults.messageTitle: Level-0: Rename to Adam, add greeting and exit

commitResults.messageBody:
Add the functionality to store user inputs and display back to the user
on command in the form of an indexed list.

User can mark a task as done or revert back the status to not done.
The corresponding task and its status are displayed as an echoed
message. The status of all tasks are shown in the list on command.

Enhance code readability through keyword changes, variable renaming and
redundancy removal, in order to follow the coding standard.

commitResults.messageTitle: Bug fix: Prevent incorrect task status changes
commitResults.messageBody:
Ensure that mark/unmark command does not erroneously revert the status
of a task.

User can add tasks with starting and ending time as events, with only
ending time as deadlines, and without starting/ending time as todos

commitResults.messageTitle: Add minimal exception handling in Adam
commitResults.messageBody:
Wrap the returned object of error-prone methods in Optional<>. This is
to deal with the removal of the add task feature previously implemented
which accepts any inputs as tasks.
Inject humor into response messages for list and add task commands.
